        {
            "_id": "5b2gROS9U3BUMTVc",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp",
            "name": "Bash It Down",
            "sort": 400000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The excruciators make a coordinated effort to shove outward with their shields, taking down opponents and impediments alike. The troop attempts to either [[/act shove]] or [[/act trip]] each enemy in a @Template[type:emanation|distance:5] and [[/act force-open]] each object in a @Template[type:emanation|distance:5]. The troop rolls a single Athletics check and compares the result to each target's appropriate DC. The troop doesn't take a penalty for not having a crowbar. It's possible for the troop to get a different degree of success for each target. The troop can't automatically Stride after any creature they successfully Shove.</p>"
                },
                "frequency": {
                    "max": 1,
                    "per": "round"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": []
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "6OHVPrLywucNXKRj",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneThreeActions.webp",
            "name": "Beat the Lawbreakers",
            "sort": 500000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The excruciators swing their maces in a coordinated melee attack against each enemy in a @Template[type:emanation|distance:5] (@Check[reflex|dc:25|basic] save). The damage depends on the number of actions. The excruciators can choose to deal nonlethal damage with this attack.</p>\n<p><span class=\"action-glyph\">1</span> @Damage[(1d6+2)[bludgeoning]]</p>\n<p><span class=\"action-glyph\">2</span> @Damage[(2d6+11)[bludgeoning]]</p>\n<p><span class=\"action-glyph\">3</span> @Damage[(3d6+14)[bludgeoning]]</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "magical"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "OFhSDDlpQpjidJ59",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp",
            "name": "Stop Where You Are",
            "sort": 600000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The excruciators draw or reload their crossbows with special hindering bolts, then launch a ranged attack in the form of a volley. This volley is a @Template[type:burst|distance:10] within 80 feet that deals @Damage[4d6[piercing]|options:area-damage] damage (@Check[reflex|dc:25|basic] save). When the dottari excruciator division is reduced to 2 or fewer segments, this area decreases to a @Template[type:burst|distance:5]. On a failure, a creature also takes a –10-foot circumstance penalty to its Speeds for 1 round. On a critical failure, a creature also gains the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Immobilized] condition ([[/act escape dc=25]]).</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
